I: Install Papirus

II: Copy content of to /usr/share/icons/Papirus/:
sudo cp -r ./* /usr/share/icons/Papirus

III: Install the Papirus-Folders script

Use this script to set color of the folders, for example:
papirus-folders -t Papirus-Dark -c oddfish

IV: Now select Papirus (or one of its variations) as the icon theme in your DE/WM's settings

Done!
